{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was so taken by this, to finally be something and someone and belong to something, that I became quite the Zionist in the [NON-ENGLISH] and very, very active.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the whole purpose, at that time, was to get as many Jews from all over the world, survivors, to come to what was then going to be, hopefully, Israel.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was Palestine then, but we all knew that there was going to be a problem with that and with the Arab world.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that they'd have to fight for their statehood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And very frankly, at that time, fighting in wars was not exactly something that I wanted to go through again.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But if that's all I had and I needed a sense of belonging, then that's what I would do.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the only surviving friend that I had before the war, who, who belonged to [NON-ENGLISH] with me, who did have parents that allowed him to go to Israel with his sister.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I wanted to go so badly, but my mother only had me and my sister.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She wasn't about to lose another son too, to any wars or anywhere, and she wanted to stay in Belgium just in case my brothers and sisters would come back, would not allow me to do so.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to make a long story short, I forged her signature and I was pretty much on my way to Israel when she discovered that forgery.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Went to the organization and told them about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was way underage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no way they were going to let me.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
